gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 119, Trail Blazers 114
gameRecap.excerpt: Minnesota defeats Portland, 119-114. For Minnesota, Rudy Gobert led the way with 25 points (9-10 FG) and 16 rebounds while Mike Conley added 19 points, seven assists, and three steals in the victory. Anfernee Simons tallied 34 points and career-high 14 assists with Duop Reath recording 26 points (five 3PM) for Portland in the losing effort. Minnesota improves to 43-19 on the season, while Portland moves to 17-43 with the loss.
